Senate Resolution 288
By: Senators Hatchett of the 50th, Strickland of the 42nd, Echols of the 49th, Robertson of
the 29th, Rahman of the 5th and others
A RESOLUTION
1 Commending the Laotian American community in Georgia and honoring the Airavata flag;
2 and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, during the Vietnam War, Laos became an unexpected battleground, with the
4 Royal Lao government, in collaboration with the Central Intelligence Agency, leading
5 Hmong and Lao forces in combat against the North Vietnamese Army and Pathet Lao
6 insurgents; and
7 WHEREAS, these forces played a crucial role in aiding and protecting United States military
8 operations in Laos, often at great personal risk, and their sacrifices remain an integral part
9 of the history of that conflict; and
10 WHEREAS, in 1975, Laos underwent a profound political transformation with the fall of
11 Vientiane and the rise of the Communist Pathet Lao government, marking the end of the
12 Kingdom of Laos and the establishment of the Lao People's Democratic Republic; and
13 WHEREAS, this sudden shift in political power created widespread fear and persecution,
14 particularly for those associated with the former regime, intellectuals, and others deemed
15 threats to the new government, forcing many Laotians to flee their homeland; and
